7. PARAMETER FILTER FORMULA - MAIN QUERY
================================================================================

This formula must be applied in:

Yearly_SLA_Report > Filtered Rows

Final formula:

= Table.SelectRows(
    Source,
    each
        [Extension] = ".xlsx"
        and Text.Contains(
            [Folder Path],
            "/Report/" & Text.Trim(Text.From(pReportFolder)) & "/" & Text.Trim(Text.From(pPeriodFolder)) & "/RAW/",
            Comparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase
        )
        and (
            if Text.Upper(Text.Trim(Text.From(pLoadMode))) = "EXACT FILE"
            then [Name] = Text.Trim(Text.From(pExactFileName))
            else true
        )
)


What this formula does:

If pLoadMode = Folder:
- Load all .xlsx files inside:
  /Report/pReportFolder/pPeriodFolder/RAW/
- Ignore pExactFileName.

If pLoadMode = Exact File:
- Load only the file where [Name] equals pExactFileName.


Example current folder mode setup:

pReportFolder  = Yearly SLA Report
pPeriodFolder  = 2026
pLoadMode      = Folder
pExactFileName = IGNORE.xlsx

This loads all .xlsx files from:

/Report/Yearly SLA Report/2026/RAW/


Example exact file setup:

pReportFolder  = Yearly SLA Report
pPeriodFolder  = 2026
pLoadMode      = Exact File
pExactFileName = JAN2026_sla.xlsx

This loads only:

JAN2026_sla.xlsx


