8. PARAMETER FILTER FORMULA - SAMPLE FILE QUERY
================================================================================

Very important fix:
When changing the SharePoint folder path, it is not enough to update only Yearly_SLA_Report.
The Sample File query must also use the same parameter filter.

Why:
Power Query Combine Files uses Sample File to understand the structure of the monthly files.
If Sample File still points to old folder, Expanded Table Column1 will fail with an error.

Error seen:

An error occurred in the 'Sample File' query.
Expression.Error: There weren't enough elements in the enumeration to complete the operation.
Details:
[Table]

Root cause:
Sample File query still used old folder path / old filter and returned zero files.

Fix:
Apply the same filter formula in:

Sample File > Filtered Rows

Formula:

= Table.SelectRows(
    Source,
    each
        [Extension] = ".xlsx"
        and Text.Contains(
            [Folder Path],
            "/Report/" & Text.Trim(Text.From(pReportFolder)) & "/" & Text.Trim(Text.From(pPeriodFolder)) & "/RAW/",
            Comparer.OrdinalIgnoreCase
        )
        and (
            if Text.Upper(Text.Trim(Text.From(pLoadMode))) = "EXACT FILE"
            then [Name] = Text.Trim(Text.From(pExactFileName))
            else true
        )
)

After applying this:
- Sample File should return a valid Binary.
- Transform Sample File should work.
- Yearly_SLA_Report > Expanded Table Column1 should show actual SLA data columns.


