19. ADD ISSUE1 COLUMN
================================================================================

Power Query column name:

Issue1

Optimized formula:

let
    desc = if [Short description] = null then "" else Text.Lower(Text.From([Short description])),
    matchedRows =
        List.Select(
            Issue1_Records,
            (r) =>
                Text.Contains(desc, r[Keyword])
                and (
                    r[Keyword2] = ""
                    or Text.Contains(desc, r[Keyword2])
                )
        )
in
    if List.IsEmpty(matchedRows)
    then "Others Issues"
    else matchedRows{0}[Category]

Logic:
- Read Issue1_Records from top to bottom.
- First match wins.
- Keyword must match.
- Keyword2 is optional.
- If no match, return Others Issues.


