22. ADD DUPLICATE COLUMN
================================================================================

Original Excel formula:

=IF(COUNTIF($A$2:[@[Number]],[@[Number]])=1,"No","Duplicate")

Meaning:
- First time Number appears = No.
- Second time onward = Duplicate.

Power Query steps:

1. Add Column > Index Column > From 1.
2. Rename Index to OriginalRow.
3. Home > Group By.
4. Choose Advanced.
5. Group by: Number.
6. New column name: AllRows.
7. Operation: All Rows.
8. Click OK.
9. Add Column > Custom Column.
10. New column name: WithOccurrence.
11. Formula:

Table.AddIndexColumn(
    Table.Sort([AllRows], {{"OriginalRow", Order.Ascending}}),
    "Occurrence",
    1,
    1,
    Int64.Type
)

12. Remove AllRows.
13. Expand WithOccurrence.
14. Untick Number because Number already exists.
15. Keep OriginalRow and Occurrence.
16. Untick Use original column name as prefix.
17. Add Custom Column named Duplicate.
18. Formula:

if [Occurrence] = 1 then "No" else "Duplicate"

19. Sort OriginalRow ascending.
20. Remove helper columns OriginalRow and Occurrence.


